description: This file implements functions for the DslhObjcoTable object, including creation, removal, object enrollment, and initialization. It appears to be part of a larger C-based project involving a DSL Home Model implementation, defining a table object with associated methods and lifecycle management.

classes.name: DSLH_OBJCO_TABLE_OBJECT
classes.description: The main object representing the Dslh Objco Table, including function pointers for lifecycle management and specific behaviors.

methods.name: ANSC_HANDLE DslhObjcoTableCreate(ANSC_HANDLE hContainerContext,ANSC_HANDLE hOwnerContext,ANSC_HANDLE hAnscReserved)
methods.description: Creates and initializes a new DslhObjco Table object, allocating memory and setting function pointers.

methods.name: ANSC_STATUS DslhObjcoTableRemove(ANSC_HANDLE hThisObject)
methods.description: Destroys a given DslhObjco Table object, freeing associated resources.

methods.name: ANSC_STATUS DslhObjcoTableEnrollObjects(ANSC_HANDLE hThisObject)
methods.description: Enrolls required nested or associated objects into the table object.

methods.name: ANSC_STATUS DslhObjcoTableInitialize(ANSC_HANDLE hThisObject)
methods.description: Initializes member fields and function pointers for the table object, including calling base class initializations.
